早在1997年12月29日，日产汽车在[[洛杉矶国际车展|洛杉矶国际车展]]推出了第一款纯电动汽车，名为日产Altra<ref name=AltraPR>{{cite web|url=http://www.theautochannel.com/news/press/date/19971229/press008845.html|title=All-New Nissan Altra EV: A Friendly, High-Tech Electric Vehicle for Everyday Life|publisher=The Auto Channel|date=1997-12-29|accessdate=2010-12-23|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805011135/http://www.theautochannel.com/news/press/date/19971229/press008845.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该车在1998年至2002年间生产，仅售出200台，且仅向公司集体出售<ref name=gutenberg>{{cite web|url=http://jcwinnie.biz/wordpress/?p=1702|title=Nissan Altra Electric Retrieved from Vacaville|publisher=After Gutenberg|date=2006-07-02|accessdate=2010-12-23|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081123035247/http://jcwinnie.biz/wordpress/?p=1702|archivedate=2008-11-23}}</ref><ref name=EVworld>{{cite web|url=http://www.evworld.com/archives/testdrives/altra.html |title=California Commuter|publisher=EV World|accessdate=2010-12-23|date=2001-01-31 |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20071117214154/http://www.evworld.com/archives/testdrives/altra.html |archivedate = 2007-11-17}}</ref>。此外，日产还开发了日产Hypermini，在1999年至2001年间生产，当时在日本仅有有限的销量，且仅为政府和企业出售<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissan-global.com/GCC/Japan/NEWS/20000113_0e.html|title=Start of Joint Field Demonstration Project Using Nissan's Hypermini|author=Nissan|publisher=Nissan Press Release|date=2000-01-13|accessdate=2011-10-29|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927122803/http://www.nissan-global.com/GCC/Japan/NEWS/20000113_0e.html|archivedate=2011-09-27}}</ref>。Hypermini于2001年至2005年亦在美国[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的街头上出现<ref>{{cite web|url=http://avt.inl.gov/pdf/uev/nissan_hypermini.pdf|title=Nissan Hypermini Urban Electric Vehicle Testing|author=Roberta Brayer and James Francfort|publisher=U.S. Department of Energy|date=January 2006|accessdate=2011-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015143439/http://avt.inl.gov/pdf/uev/nissan_hypermini.pdf|archive-date=2011-10-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

直至2009年，日产推出了基于[[日產Tiida|日產Tiida]]研发的EV-11电动原型车，该车使用全电动动力传动系统，包括一个80千瓦（110马力）/280N·m（210lb·ft）的电动马达、24千瓦时的锂离子电池组，根据美国环境保护署所提供的数据，该车最大续航里程为175公里（109英里，根据城市工况）。该车还提供导航系统，并通过手机连接到日产的数据中心进行汽车远程控制和监测<ref name=EV11>{{cite web |last=Abuelsamid |first=Sam |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2009/07/27/nissan-shows-off-new-versa-based-electric-vehicle-prototype/ |title=Nissan shows off new Versa-based electric vehicle prototype |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=2009-07-27 |accessdate=2010-12-11 |archive-date=2018-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712122034/https://www.autoblog.com/2009/07/27/nissan-shows-off-new-versa-based-electric-vehicle-prototype/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此前，日产还推出了EV-01、EV-02的电动测试车<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/26051059/|title=Nissan shows test models of electric car, hybrid|publisher=MSNBC News|agency=Associated Press|date=2008-08-06|accessdate=2010-04-25|archive-date=2012-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103222148/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/26051059/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-13746_7-10210982-48.html|title=Test-driving the Nissan EV-02 electric car|publisher=cnet|author=Antuan Goodwin|date=2009-04-02|accessdate=2010-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413171912/http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-13746_7-10210982-48.html|archive-date=2010-04-13|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

2009年8月2日，日产在横滨总部推出了EV-11的量产版，并宣布自2010年底起，在北美和日本市场销售<ref>{{cite web |last=Paukert |first=Chris |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2009/08/01/2010-nissan-leaf-electric-car-in-person-in-depth-and-u-s-b/ |title=2010 Nissan Leaf electric car: In person, in depth – and U.S. bound |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=2009-08-01 |accessdate=2010-12-11 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112024200/https://www.autoblog.com/2009/08/01/2010-nissan-leaf-electric-car-in-person-in-depth-and-u-s-b/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nissan unveils PR">{{cite press release |title=Nissan unveils "LEAF" - the world's first electric car designed for affordability and real-world requirements |url=http://www.nissan-global.com/EN/NEWS/2009/_STORY/090802-02-e.html |publisher=Nissan |date=2009-08-02 |accessdate=2010-05-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65LJtz8ff?url=http://www.nissan-global.com/EN/NEWS/2009/_STORY/090802-02-e.html |archivedate=2012-02-10 }}</ref>。

