===外观设计===
日产聆风的外观以“智能流动体”为设计理念<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissan.com.cn/minisite/leaf/Exterior02.php|title=外观 > 外饰|publisher=日产中国|accessdate=2015年11月26日|archive-date=2015年3月30日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330163332/http://www.nissan.com.cn/minisite/leaf/Exterior02.php|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，其前方采用尖锐的V型设计，并使用低能耗的LED[[前大灯|前大灯]]和[[尾灯|尾灯]]，以营造出独特的蓝色内部反光设计。而特别设计的车头轮廓引导车头气流远离[[后视镜|后视镜]]，从而降低风噪声和空气阻力<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pVwtwhvmK0I |title=Nissan Leaf electric vehicle – MPG-o-Matic! 7m20s |author=YouTube |date=2010-01-31 |publisher=[[YouTube|YouTube]] |accessdate=2010-05-28 |archive-date=2020-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813144337/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pVwtwhvmK0I |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该车的底部备有空气动力学镶板，以减轻空气阻力，并提高尽可能多的空气动力性能<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.motortrend.com/roadtests/alternative/1007_2011_nissan_leaf_vs_2012_mitsubishi_i_miev/exterior.html |title=Quick Comparison: 2011 Nissan Leaf vs. 2012 Mitsubishi i-MiEV |date=2010-08-03 |work=Motor Trend |accessdate=2010-08-03 |archive-date=2012-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010224743/http://www.motortrend.com/roadtests/alternative/1007_2011_nissan_leaf_vs_2012_mitsubishi_i_miev/exterior.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。根据日产的官方数据，2011款日产聆风[[风阻系数|风阻系数]]为0.29，2013款则降低为0.28<ref name=2013MYLeafUS>{{cite web|url=http://www.greencarreports.com/news/1081547_2013-nissan-leaf-longer-range-faster-charging-leather-seats-and-more-all-the-upgrades|title=2013 Nissan Leaf: Longer Range, Faster Charging, Leather Seats, And More: All The Upgrades|author=John Voelcker|publisher=Green Car Reports|date=2013-01-09|accessdate=2013-02-10|archive-date=2021-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124101823/https://www.greencarreports.com/news/1081547_2013-nissan-leaf-longer-range-faster-charging-leather-seats-and-more-all-the-upgrades|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===动力===
日产聆风使用EM61型[[永磁同步马达|永磁同步马达]]<ref name="TechOn"/>，最大功率为{{convert|80|kW|hp|abbr=on}}，最大扭矩为{{convert|280|Nm|ftlb|abbr=on|-1}}<ref name=NissanSpecs/>，并配备24kWh[[锂离子电池|锂离子电池]]<ref name=EPA2014/15/16/>，可提供{{convert|90|kW|hp|abbr=on}}的电力输出<ref name="#1"/>。

2011/12款日产聆风的极速为{{convert|150|km/h|mph|abbr=on}}，每小时百公里加速时间为9.9秒（非官方测试数据）<ref name=EdmundsTest/>。

===电池===
日产聆风采用超薄层叠式紧凑型24kWh[[锂离子电池|锂离子电池]]（总容量，实际可用电池容量约为21.3kWh<ref>{{cite news |url=http://insideevs.com/real-world-test-2013-nissan-leaf-range-vs-2012-nissan-leaf-range/ |title=Real World Test: 2013 Nissan LEAF Range vs 2012 Nissan LEAF Range (w/Video) |first=Tony |last=Williams |work=Inside EVs |date=2013-02-25 |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2018-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106201559/https://insideevs.com/real-world-test-2013-nissan-leaf-range-vs-2012-nissan-leaf-range/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.eere.energy.gov/vehiclesandfuels/pdfs/merit_review_2012/veh_sys_sim/vss030_lohsebusch_2012_o.pdf |title=Advanced Technology VehicleLab Benchmarking – Level 1 |publisher=Argonne National Laboratory |first1=Henning |last1=Lohse-Busch |first2=Michael |last2=Duoba |page=9 |date=2012-05-15 |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306012237/http://www1.eere.energy.gov/vehiclesandfuels/pdfs/merit_review_2012/veh_sys_sim/vss030_lohsebusch_2012_o.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissan.com.cn/minisite/leaf/Charm_LEAF01.php|title=魅力LEAF > 产品声明|publisher=日产中国|accessdate=2015年11月26日|archive-date=2016年5月7日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507182631/http://www.nissan.com.cn/minisite/leaf/Charm_LEAF01.php|dead-url=yes}}</ref>），该电池由日产、[[NEC|NEC]]及NEC能源设备在日本[[神奈川县|神奈川县]][[座間市|座間市]]合资创立的汽车能源供应公司（Automotive Energy Supply Corporation，AESC）组装<ref>{{cite news |url=http://money.cnn.com/galleries/2010/fortune/1002/gallery.nissan_leaf.fortune/index.html |title=Nissan's Leaf up close |author=CNN |date=2010-02-17 |accessdate=2010-05-28 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126143928/https://money.cnn.com/galleries/2010/fortune/1002/gallery.nissan_leaf.fortune/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Production1010>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissan-global.com/EN/NEWS/2010/_STORY/101022-01-e.html|title=Production of 100% Electric, Zero-Emission Nissan LEAF begins at Oppama, Japan|date=2010-10-22|publisher=Nissan News|accessdate=2011-01-06|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110101234458/http://www.nissan-global.com/EN/NEWS/2010/_STORY/101022-01-e.html|archivedate=2011-01-01}}</ref><ref name=AutoblogGreen100527>{{cite web|last=Blanco|first=Sebastian|title=Details on Nissan Leaf battery pack, including how recharging speed affects battery life|date=2010-05-27|url=http://green.autoblog.com/2010/05/27/details-on-nissan-leaf-battery-pack-including-how-recharging-sp/|publisher=AutoblogGreen|accessdate=2011-05-30|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208230644/http://green.autoblog.com/2010/05/27/details-on-nissan-leaf-battery-pack-including-how-recharging-sp/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。电池和控制模块的总重量为{{convert|480|lb|kg|abbr=on|disp=flip|0}}<ref>{{cite web |author=Paul Weissler |url=http://www.sae.org/mags/aei/7714 |work=Automotive Engineering International Online |publisher=SAE International |title=Leaf to be sold with battery pack at C-segment price |date=2010-03-12 |accessdate=2010-04-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710100104/http://www.sae.org/mags/aei/7714 |archivedate=2011年7月10日 |df= }}</ref>。

该电池属于该车最重的部分，其电池位于下面的座椅和后排脚部空间，可保持尽可能低的重心，亦可增加车辆的结构刚度<ref name=EdmundsTest/><ref name=AutoblogGreen100527/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insideline.com/nissan/leaf/2011/2011-nissan-leaf-prototype-japan-first-drive.html|publisher=Edmunds Inside Line|title=2011 Nissan Leaf Prototype (Japan) First Drive|author=Peter Nunn|date=2010-06-23|accessdate=2011-01-01|archive-date=2012-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104154344/http://www.insideline.com/nissan/leaf/2011/2011-nissan-leaf-prototype-japan-first-drive.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该电池预计在使用10年后，可保留70％到80％的容量，但它的实际使用寿命会因充电频率、驾驶方式和环境因素而出现差异，不过日产官方表示日产表示，随着时间的推移，电池容量会逐渐下降，但在正常使用的情况下，电池可使用10年以上<ref name=HybridC0510>{{cite web|url=http://www.hybridcars.com/news/13-key-questions-and-answers-about-nissan-leaf-battery-pack-and-ordering-28007.html|publisher=HybridCars.com|date=2010-05-27|title=13 Key Questions and Answers about Nissan Leaf Battery Pack and Ordering|accessdate=2010-05-31|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100530051016/http://www.hybridcars.com/news/13-key-questions-and-answers-about-nissan-leaf-battery-pack-and-ordering-28007.html|archivedate=2010年5月30日|df=}}</ref><ref name=Nissan10yr>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissanusa.com/leaf-electric-car/faq/list/technology|publisher=Nissan USA|title=Nissan Leaf Technology FAQ|quote=Q: How many charging cycles can the energy storage device survive? A: Like all lithium ion batteries, the Nissan LEAF™ battery will experience gradual capacity loss over time. We expect the battery to last over 10 years, however, there may be a gradual loss of capacity of 30% or more depending on your driving patterns, and the effect on your battery. The battery can be used afterward for storage applications.|accessdate=2012-06-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717142355/http://www.nissanusa.com/leaf-electric-car/faq/list/technology|archivedate=2011年7月17日|df=}}</ref>。在美国，2011/12款日产聆风可获得8年或{{convert|100000|mi|km|abbr=in|order=flip}}（以先到者为准）免费电池保修<ref name=GCC072710>{{cite web|url=http://www.greencarcongress.com/2010/07/nissan-to-warranty-leaf-battery-for-8-years-100000-miles-.html#more|title=Nissan to Warranty LEAF Battery for 8 Years, 100,000 Miles|publisher=Green Car Congress|date=2010-07-27|accessdate=2010-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708213639/https://www.greencarcongress.com/2010/07/nissan-to-warranty-leaf-battery-for-8-years-100000-miles-.html#more|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=CNN072710>{{cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2010/07/27/autos/volt_price/index.htm?hpt=T2|title=Chevy Volt priced at $41,000|author=Peter Valdes-Dapena|publisher=CNN Money|accessdate=2010-07-27|date=2010-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708213655/https://money.cnn.com/2010/07/27/autos/volt_price/index.htm?hpt=T2|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由于美国部分地区夏季气候炎热，导致部分车主发现电池出现电池容量下降，日产美国已于2012年1月宣布，所有2011-2013款日产聆风均延长其免费电池保修期限<ref name=BatteryUK>{{cite web|url=http://www.green-car-guide.com/new-nissan-leaf.html|title=New Nissan Leaf|author=Green Car Guide|publisher=GreenCarGuide.com|date=2013-03-05|accessdate=2013-03-12|archive-date=2013-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619123634/http://www.green-car-guide.com/new-nissan-leaf.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。对于2011款车型，日产还建议车主正确使用电池以延长其使用寿命<ref name=OwnManual>{{cite web|url=http://www.nissan-techinfo.com/refgh0v/og/Leaf/2011-Nissan-Leaf.pdf|title=2011 LEAF Owner's Manual|publisher=Nissan|date=|accessdate=2011-05-14|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315013848/https://www.nissan-techinfo.com/refgh0v/og/Leaf/2011-Nissan-Leaf.pdf|dead-url=no}} ''See pages EV2 and EV22 - EV Overview''.</ref>。

在美国，该车在上市之初的电池的更换费为18,000美元<ref>{{cite web|url=http://green.autoblog.com/2010/05/15/nissan-leaf-profitable-by-year-three-battery-cost-closer-to-18/|title=Nissan Leaf profitable by year three; battery cost closer to $18,000|publisher=AutoblogGreen|date=2010-05-15|accessdate=2010-05-15|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030160224/http://green.autoblog.com/2010/05/15/nissan-leaf-profitable-by-year-three-battery-cost-closer-to-18/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2015年调整为每千瓦时300美元<ref name="Brockman">{{cite web |url=http://www.mynissanleaf.com/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=17168 |title=Update on Nissan LEAF Battery Replacement |first=Brian |last=Brockman |publisher=MyNissanLeaf |date=2014-06-07 |accessdate=2013-07-10 |archive-date=2021-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120013459/https://mynissanleaf.com/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=17168 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，对于不在保修期范围内的车辆，费用为5,500美元<ref>{{cite web | url=http://cleantechnica.com/2015/03/25/99-99-nissan-leaf-batteries-still-operation/ | title=99.99% Of Nissan LEAF Batteries Still In Operation | accessdate=2015-11-15 | archive-date=2015-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208135929/http://cleantechnica.com/2015/03/25/99-99-nissan-leaf-batteries-still-operation/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

